10:58.450 --> 11:00.486
...that I didn't.

11:01.119 --> 11:04.282
He said I didn't know them
because I never cared enough to ask.

11:06.708 --> 11:08.744
I'm sorry...

11:09.586 --> 11:11.167
...that I never asked.

11:12.798 --> 11:14.629
It's okay.

11:17.511 --> 11:19.172
Are you two happy together?

11:20.180 --> 11:21.841
Yeah.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.596
Yeah, I think we're gonna be.

11:25.894 --> 11:28.101
Then I'm happy for you.

11:30.732 --> 11:32.313
Thank you.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.817
Do me a favor, will you?

11:35.988 --> 11:37.774
Yeah, anything.

11:38.198 --> 11:41.281
Just make sure that Sookie gets home safe.

11:41.451 --> 11:42.907
Of course.

11:43.537 --> 11:45.368
Where are you going?

11:45.956 --> 11:47.571
Jess?

11:53.672 --> 11:54.957
[MAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY OVER TV]

11:55.173 --> 11:56.959
[DISHES CLATTERING]

12:00.137 --> 12:01.502
[SIGHS]

12:02.639 --> 12:05.506
Look, I'm really proud of you
for being a hero and all, Hoyt...

12:05.684 --> 12:07.549
...but I think that we need to talk.

12:07.728 --> 12:11.346
-What about?
-What about? About last night, Hoyt.

12:11.815 --> 12:13.976
About you not wanting to have children.

12:14.151 --> 12:17.018
You owe me an explanation.
Don't you think that I deserve that?

12:18.322 --> 12:19.812
I love you, Brigette.

12:19.990 --> 12:22.072
If I wanted to have kids...

12:23.076 --> 12:24.907
...I would want to have kids with you.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.818
| just--

12:26.997 --> 12:29.283
I don't know if that's where I'm at.

12:30.125 --> 12:32.741
That's all. That's all it is.

12:36.882 --> 12:38.247
[SIGHS]

12:40.928 --> 12:43.385
Who was that redhead last night?

12:44.723 --> 12:46.509
What redhead?

12:46.683 --> 12:47.889
The vampire.

12:48.060 --> 12:51.177
The one who got all googly-eyed
after you saved her life?

12:51.355 --> 12:54.768
All Southern with her eyelashes
that go on for days.

12:54.942 --> 12:57.604
Brigette, I've never seen her
before last night.

12:57.778 --> 13:00.144
I've never laid eyes
on a redheaded vampire before.

13:00.322 --> 13:02.984
-But you know who she is now, don't you?
-Oh, fuck.

13:03.158 --> 13:05.240
-What?
-Could we just talk...

13:05.410 --> 13:06.991
...without you hounding on me?

13:07.162 --> 13:09.995
Where were you today
while I was here packing up this house...

13:10.165 --> 13:13.123
...so you wouldn't have to deal
with the emotional burden of it?

13:13.293 --> 13:14.908
Where were you?

13:15.087 --> 13:17.123
l was with Officer Stackhouse.

13:17.297 --> 13:20.460
You were with Jason? All day?

13:20.634 --> 13:24.377
You didn't go anywhere else?
You didn't do anything else?

13:24.972 --> 13:26.712
Okay.

13:29.142 --> 13:30.803
Okay, I saw her.

13:30.978 --> 13:32.843
-Goddamn it, Hoyt.
-No, goddamn nothing.

13:33.021 --> 13:34.807
Listen, I've never seen her before...

13:34.982 --> 13:37.849
...and I don't have any idea who she is,
and that's the truth.

13:38.026 --> 13:42.315
I'm sitting up with Jason
at Merlotte's or Bellefleur's--

13:42.489 --> 13:46.027
Whatever the hell it is they call it now,
and he tells me her maker's dying.

13:46.201 --> 13:48.692
Okay, so you don't know her,
but you do know her maker?

13:48.870 --> 13:51.907
Yes. Yeah, he's the
first vampire that I ever met.

13:52.082 --> 13:54.915
He's always been good to me
and had a super interesting life.

13:55.085 --> 13:57.622
The man is dying. I wanted to help out.

13:58.255 --> 14:00.917
So I went to the clinic,
gave blood, took it over there...

14:01.091 --> 14:03.582
...so he'd have something to eat,
that's the truth.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.591
You swear you're not lying to me, Hoyt?

14:06.179 --> 14:08.636
I swear I'm not lying to you.

14:12.269 --> 14:14.601
-l'm sorry.
-lt's okay.

14:15.147 --> 14:16.762
No, it's not.

14:16.940 --> 14:21.559
I know you better than that. I guess
I just don't know you here or something.

14:22.112 --> 14:26.276
-Honey, it's okay.
-Mm-hm.

14:26.908 --> 14:29.320
I'll make us some dinner,
we'll forget all about it.

14:29.536 --> 14:30.525
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:30.704 --> 14:31.784
JESSICA:
Hoyt?

14:33.123 --> 14:34.158
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:34.332 --> 14:38.416
Hoyt, can you open the door, please?
I really-- I need to talk to you.

14:38.628 --> 14:41.791
-Who is that?
-I don't know, baby. I don't know.

14:42.007 --> 14:43.417
[SIGHS]

14:47.763 --> 14:49.424
What do you want?

14:49.598 --> 14:51.589
I'm sorry, Hoyt. I'm really sorry.

14:51.767 --> 14:53.428
-This is 30--
-Jesus, Jess. What's the matter?

14:53.602 --> 14:55.888
Huh. Oh, so you do know her, then?

14:56.063 --> 15:00.181
Look, I know that I should not be here...

15:00.734 --> 15:02.065
...but please, can I come in?

15:02.235 --> 15:04.442
No, you may not.
Hoyt, you are a fucking liar.

15:04.613 --> 15:06.444
JESSICA:
He's not lying.

15:07.074 --> 15:08.530
He's not.

15:08.700 --> 15:11.191
I know him, but he doesn't know me.

15:11.369 --> 15:14.031
-That's not even possible.
-Yes, it is. Trust me.

15:16.166 --> 15:19.579
That's what I came here for.
I came here to tell him-- To tell you....

15:21.296 --> 15:23.412
-Tell me what?
-About us.

15:26.301 --> 15:28.633
Hoyt, you and me, we used to be...

15:29.888 --> 15:30.923
...together.

15:32.349 --> 15:34.635
-What?
-We lived together...

15:36.353 --> 15:39.140
...and we were so, so happy.

15:40.315 --> 15:42.180
And then I went...

15:42.359 --> 15:44.475
-...and I fucked it up.
-You need to leave.

15:44.653 --> 15:47.315
-Hang on a second.
-No, I'm not gonna hang on a second.

15:47.489 --> 15:51.778
Look, I am so confused right now and
I don't know what the fuck is going on...

15:51.952 --> 15:54.614
...but I do know
that I don't want to listen to it.

15:55.080 --> 15:56.160
I can't.

15:56.665 --> 16:01.125
If you want to listen to it, then
you can feel free to, but do it outside.

16:01.378 --> 16:03.915
And go out there knowing
if you walk out on me now...

16:04.089 --> 16:05.454
...you and me are through.

16:06.550 --> 16:07.790
Do you understand?

16:19.604 --> 16:21.435
I'm sorry, Brigette.

16:27.737 --> 16:29.193
[GASPS]

16:29.406 --> 16:31.397
[CRYING]

16:34.327 --> 16:35.988
HOYT:
Jessica?

16:37.038 --> 16:39.199
You wanna tell me what's going on?

16:42.252 --> 16:44.538
Bill released me tonight.

16:46.089 --> 16:48.956
Jesus, I'm sorry.

16:49.134 --> 16:50.670
Why?

16:51.261 --> 16:53.217
There's a cure...

16:54.556 --> 16:56.262
...but he wouldn't drink it.

16:57.934 --> 17:01.097
-I'm confused.
-Yeah, so am I.

17:02.439 --> 17:05.181
Because it was right there.

17:05.817 --> 17:10.436
Salvation was right there
and he wouldn't take it.

17:12.199 --> 17:13.939
-How come?
-I don't know.

17:15.035 --> 17:19.028
And I don't think that he even knows,
but I-- I could understand.

17:19.664 --> 17:22.326
I could understand someone
accepting their fate...

17:22.500 --> 17:25.287
...if they had to, but if they don't?

17:26.087 --> 17:28.123
That I don't understand.

17:30.342 --> 17:32.924
But you thought I would understand.

17:34.221 --> 17:37.054
I thought you would understand me.

17:40.018 --> 17:43.385
You were the first man
that I ever really loved.

17:45.357 --> 17:48.474
I'm really sorry that I fucked
everything up with your girlfriend.

17:48.652 --> 17:51.268
I mean, she seems
really nice and everything.

17:51.446 --> 17:54.153
It's just that I knew that you were here...

17:54.783 --> 17:57.775
...and I couldn't think of anyone else
I would want to be with...

17:57.953 --> 17:59.989
...on a night like tonight.

18:02.666 --> 18:05.453
And that is the most
selfish thing I have ever heard.

18:05.627 --> 18:07.993
Well, maybe it is.

18:10.090 --> 18:11.500
But for whatever reason...

18:11.675 --> 18:14.212
...does it really fucking matter right now?

18:18.515 --> 18:21.257
I want you to see if you can
try to catch your breath.

18:22.310 --> 18:23.470
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

18:25.647 --> 18:28.639
